---
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';

import { isBlogPublished } from '../../lib/blogGate';
import BlogCrossLinks from '../../components/BlogCrossLinks.astro';
const slug = Astro.url.pathname.replace('/blog/', '').replace(/\/$/, '');
const isPublished = await isBlogPublished(slug);
if (!isPublished) return Astro.redirect('/404');
---
<BlogLayout title="How to Set Up a Scrabble Game — Board, Tiles & First Move Rules" description="Complete guide to setting up a Scrabble game. Learn board layout, tile distribution, how to draw starting tiles, first move rules. Free, instant results." keywords="set up scrabble game, scrabble setup guide, scrabble board layout, scrabble tile distribution, first move scrabble, scrabble rules beginners">
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Article",
    "headline": "How to Set Up a Scrabble Game — Board, Tiles & First Move Rules",
    "datePublished": "2026-06-15",
    "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com", "url": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/" },
    "url": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/setting-up-a-scrabble-game/"
  })} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "How many tiles does each player draw at the start of Scrabble?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Each player draws 7 tiles from the bag at the start of Scrabble. After each turn, players replenish their rack back to 7 tiles until the bag is empty." }},
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "Who goes first in Scrabble?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Each player draws one tile from the bag. The player whose tile is closest to A goes first. Blanks beat all letters. After determining order, tiles are returned to the bag and each player draws their 7 starting tiles." }},
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "Does the first word in Scrabble have to cover the center star?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes. The first word must be placed so that one of its letters covers the center star square (marked with a ★). This square counts as a double word score for the first player." }}
    ]
  })} />

  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4">
    <article class="prose dark:prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <!-- Breadcrumb -->
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mb-6" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
        <a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-amber-600">Blog</a>
        <span class="mx-2">›</span>
        <a href="/blog/beginner-guides/" class="hover:text-amber-600">Beginner Guides</a>
        <span class="mx-2">›</span>
        <span class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">Setting Up</span>
      </nav>

      <BlogCrossLinks title="How to Set Up a Scrabble Game — Board, Tiles & First Move Rules" />

      <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mb-6">Published June 15, 2026 · 5 min read</p>

      <p class="lead text-lg text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-8">Setting up Scrabble correctly takes less than two minutes, but getting the details right matters — especially the first move rules and tile drawing process. Whether you're teaching someone new or refreshing your memory, here's the complete setup guide.</p>

      <!-- Stat strip -->
      <div class="border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10 rounded-lg p-4 mb-8 grid grid-cols-3 gap-4 text-center">
        <div><p class="text-2xl font-bold text-amber-400">100</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Total Tiles</p></div>
        <div><p class="text-2xl font-bold text-amber-400">7</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Tiles per Player</p></div>
        <div><p class="text-2xl font-bold text-amber-400">15×15</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Board Grid</p></div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Step 1: Prepare the Board</h2>
      <p>Unfold the Scrabble board and place it on a flat surface between the players. The board is a 15×15 grid with premium squares marked in different colours:</p>
      <div class="overflow-x-auto my-6">
        <table class="w-full text-sm">
          <thead><tr class="border-b border-gray-700"><th class="text-left py-2 px-3">Square Type</th><th class="text-left py-2 px-3">Colour</th><th class="text-left py-2 px-3">Effect</th><th class="text-right py-2 px-3">Count</th></tr></thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800"><td class="py-2 px-3">Double Letter (DL)</td><td class="py-2 px-3">Light Blue</td><td class="py-2 px-3">Letter value ×2</td><td class="py-2 px-3 text-right text-amber-600 font-bold">24</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800/50"><td class="py-2 px-3">Triple Letter (TL)</td><td class="py-2 px-3">Dark Blue</td><td class="py-2 px-3">Letter value ×3</td><td class="py-2 px-3 text-right text-amber-600 font-bold">12</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800"><td class="py-2 px-3">Double Word (DW)</td><td class="py-2 px-3">Pink</td><td class="py-2 px-3">Word total ×2</td><td class="py-2 px-3 text-right text-amber-600 font-bold">17</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800/50"><td class="py-2 px-3">Triple Word (TW)</td><td class="py-2 px-3">Red</td><td class="py-2 px-3">Word total ×3</td><td class="py-2 px-3 text-right text-amber-600 font-bold">8</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800"><td class="py-2 px-3">Center Star (★)</td><td class="py-2 px-3">Pink/Star</td><td class="py-2 px-3">DW for first word</td><td class="py-2 px-3 text-right text-amber-600 font-bold">1</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
      <p>Each player should have a tile rack in front of them. Place the score sheet and a pen nearby.</p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Step 2: Prepare the Tile Bag</h2>
      <p>Place all 100 tiles into the cloth bag and mix them thoroughly. The standard English Scrabble set contains:</p>
      <div class="border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
        <p class="font-semibold text-purple-300 mb-2">Tile Distribution (100 tiles total)</p>
        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-300 space-y-1 list-disc pl-4">
          <li><strong>9 tiles:</strong> A, I</li>
          <li><strong>8 tiles:</strong> O</li>
          <li><strong>6 tiles:</strong> E, N, R, T</li>
          <li><strong>4 tiles:</strong> D, L, S, U</li>
          <li><strong>3 tiles:</strong> G</li>
          <li><strong>2 tiles:</strong> B, C, F, H, M, P, V, W, Y, Blank</li>
          <li><strong>1 tile:</strong> J, K, Q, X, Z</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Step 3: Determine Who Goes First</h2>
      <p>Each player draws one tile from the bag without looking. The player whose tile is closest to the letter A goes first. If a player draws a blank tile, they automatically go first (blanks beat all letters). After determining turn order, return these tiles to the bag and remix.</p>
      <div class="border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
        <p class="font-semibold text-purple-300 mb-2">Tie-Breaking</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300">If two players draw the same letter, both return their tiles to the bag and draw again. Continue until someone draws a letter closer to A.</p>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Step 4: Draw Starting Tiles</h2>
      <p>Starting with the first player, each person draws 7 tiles from the bag and places them on their rack. Keep your tiles hidden from other players. You should now have:</p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-sm text-gray-300 my-4">
        <li>Board set up with all premium squares visible</li>
        <li>Each player holding 7 tiles on their rack</li>
        <li>Remaining tiles in the bag (86 tiles for a 2-player game)</li>
        <li>Score sheet ready with player names</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Step 5: The First Move</h2>
      <p>The first player must follow these rules for the opening word:</p>
      <div class="overflow-x-auto my-6">
        <table class="w-full text-sm">
          <thead><tr class="border-b border-gray-700"><th class="text-left py-2 px-3">Rule</th><th class="text-left py-2 px-3">Details</th></tr></thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800"><td class="py-2 px-3 font-semibold">Cover the center star</td><td class="py-2 px-3">One letter of the word must sit on the ★ square</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800/50"><td class="py-2 px-3 font-semibold">Minimum 2 letters</td><td class="py-2 px-3">The first word must be at least 2 tiles long</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800"><td class="py-2 px-3 font-semibold">Read left-right or top-down</td><td class="py-2 px-3">Words must read in a valid direction</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800/50"><td class="py-2 px-3 font-semibold">Double word score applies</td><td class="py-2 px-3">The center ★ counts as a DW square — first word is doubled</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800"><td class="py-2 px-3 font-semibold">Draw replacement tiles</td><td class="py-2 px-3">After playing, draw from the bag until you have 7 tiles again</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Keeping Score</h2>
      <p>After each word is played, the active player announces their score and the designated scorekeeper records it. Calculate scores by:</p>
      <div class="border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
        <p class="font-semibold text-purple-300 mb-2">Scoring Steps</p>
        <ol class="text-sm text-gray-300 space-y-1 list-decimal pl-4">
          <li>Add up the face value of each letter in the word</li>
          <li>Apply any letter multipliers (DL or TL) to individual tiles</li>
          <li>Apply any word multipliers (DW or TW) to the total</li>
          <li>If you used all 7 tiles in one turn, add 50 bonus points (bingo!)</li>
          <li>Premium squares only count the first time they're covered</li>
        </ol>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Common Setup Mistakes to Avoid</h2>
      <p>New players often make these errors during setup that can cause confusion later in the game:</p>
      <div class="border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
        <p class="font-semibold text-purple-300 mb-2">Avoid These Errors</p>
        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-300 space-y-1 list-disc pl-4">
          <li><strong>Not mixing tiles thoroughly</strong> — clumped tiles from previous games give unfair starting hands</li>
          <li><strong>Forgetting the blank tiles</strong> — the bag should have exactly 100 tiles including 2 blanks</li>
          <li><strong>Skipping the turn-order draw</strong> — randomly deciding who goes first gives an unfair advantage</li>
          <li><strong>Misreading the center square</strong> — the ★ is a Double Word, not Triple Word</li>
          <li><strong>Drawing too many tiles</strong> — always count to exactly 7, no more</li>
          <li><strong>Placing the board unevenly</strong> — a sloped surface causes tiles to slide mid-game</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <p>Once setup is complete, play proceeds clockwise. Each player's turn consists of placing a word, calculating the score, drawing replacement tiles, and passing to the next player. The game ends when the tile bag is empty and one player uses their last tile — or when all players pass consecutively.</p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Quick Setup Checklist</h2>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-sm text-gray-300 my-4 space-y-1">
        <li>✅ Board unfolded flat on a stable surface</li>
        <li>✅ All 100 tiles thoroughly mixed in the bag</li>
        <li>✅ Each player has a tile rack</li>
        <li>✅ Turn order determined by closest-to-A draw</li>
        <li>✅ Drawn tiles returned and remixed before starting</li>
        <li>✅ Each player draws exactly 7 tiles</li>
        <li>✅ Score sheet ready with player names</li>
        <li>✅ Dictionary accessible for challenges (physical or app)</li>
      </ul>

      <!-- Cross-links -->
      <div class="border border-indigo-500/30 bg-indigo-950/10 rounded-lg p-4 my-8">
        <p class="font-semibold text-indigo-300 mb-2">Related Guides</p>
        <ul class="text-sm space-y-1">
          <li><a href="/blog/scrabble-rules-explained/" class="text-indigo-400 hover:underline">Scrabble Rules Explained →</a></li>
          <li><a href="/blog/scrabble-scoring-guide/" class="text-indigo-400 hover:underline">Scrabble Scoring Guide →</a></li>
          <li><a href="/blog/understanding-premium-squares/" class="text-indigo-400 hover:underline">Understanding Premium Squares →</a></li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <!-- Related articles -->
      <aside class="border-t border-gray-700 pt-6 mt-10">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 mb-3">You might also like</p>
        <ul class="text-sm space-y-2">
          <li><a href="/blog/how-to-play-scrabble/" class="text-amber-500 hover:underline">How to Play Scrabble</a></li>
          <li><a href="/blog/beginner-scrabble-strategy/" class="text-amber-500 hover:underline">Beginner Scrabble Strategy</a></li>
          <li><a href="/blog/scrabble-tile-bag-distribution/" class="text-amber-500 hover:underline">Scrabble Tile Bag Distribution</a></li>
        </ul>
      </aside>

      <!-- CTA -->
      <div class="bg-gradient-to-r from-amber-50 to-orange-50 dark:from-amber-900/20 dark:to-orange-900/20 rounded-xl p-6 text-center my-10">
        <p class="text-lg font-semibold mb-2">Ready to play? Find the best words from your rack</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-4">Enter your 7 tiles and get instant scoring suggestions.</p>
        <a href="/" class="inline-block bg-amber-600 hover:bg-amber-700 text-white font-medium py-2 px-6 rounded-lg transition-colors">Try the Word Finder →</a>
      </div>

      <div class="text-center mt-8">
        <a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-500 hover:text-amber-500 transition-colors">← Back to Blog</a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
